comments: Composite numbers not divisible by 2 or 5. - _Lekraj Beedassy_, Jul 05 2004Composite numbers ending in 1, 3, 7 or 9 are values (some shared within sets, because some values are numbers with multiple factors) of the following sets of binomial products:  {(10x+3)*(10y+7), (10x+11)*(10y+11), (10x+19)*(10y+19)}, {(10x+3)*(10y+11), (10x+7)*(10y+9)},  {(10x+3)*(10y+9), (10x+7)*(10y+11)}, and  {(10x+3)*(10y+3), (10x+7)*(10y+7), (10x+11)*(10y+19)}, with x, y integers >= 0. - _Marvin Y. Hubble_, Jul 12 2013 and May 12 2014.
